description_narrative:
1. To test two new technologies which, by leapfrogging conventional diagnostic approaches, could bring fast and precise diagnosis of Epstein Barr Virus Lymphoma to sub-Sahara Africa; 
2. To generate viral and tumour sequence information to inform the design of future screening programmes and vaccine development; 
3. To perform a clinical validation of our diagnostic tools and then a controlled before-after study to test whether these speed up diagnosis, increase the number of children diagnosed and treated, and ultimately improve survival compared to gold-standard pathology.
